---
name: Sync.so Webhook + 8-min Per-Shot Watchdog (Stage 5 B.1 + B.4)
description: poll-dialog-shots registers a webhook URL per Sync.so job; sync-so-webhook receives terminal status, patches dialog_shots[idx] and fire-and-forgets poll-dialog-shots; per-shot stuck-after-8min check inside poll-dialog-shots; legacy twoshot-lipsync-watchdog timeout shortened 12→8 min with clip_error 'sync_so_timeout_8min'
type: feature
---

**B.1 Webhook:**
- `poll-dialog-shots` builds `webhookUrl = ${SUPABASE_URL}/functions/v1/sync-so-webhook?scene_id={id}` via `appendWebhookToken(...)` (reuses existing `WEBHOOK_SHARED_SECRET`, no new secret).
- Passed into Sync.so v2 `/generate` payload as both `webhookUrl` and `webhook_url`.
- `sync-so-webhook` (verify_jwt=false) verifies the `?token=` shared secret, finds the scene by `scene_id` hint or by scanning in-flight scenes for the `sync_job_id`, patches `dialog_shots.shots[idx]` (status=ready+output_url OR failed with `sync_${STATUS}` error), then fire-and-forgets `poll-dialog-shots` for that scene. Always returns 200 so Sync.so never retry-storms.
- pg_cron polling stays as safety net — webhook is purely additive.

**B.4 Per-Shot 8-min Watchdog:**
- Inside `poll-dialog-shots` Step 1b: any shot with `status='lipsyncing'` whose `started_at` is >8 min old is marked `failed` with `error='sync_so_timeout_8min: job <id> stuck <Xs>'`. Refund happens via existing `state.refunded` boolean in `refundIfNeeded` (idempotent).
- Legacy two-shot pipeline: `twoshot-lipsync-watchdog` `STALE_SYNC_POLL_MS` shortened from 12 → 8 min; clip_error string is now `sync_so_timeout_8min`.

**Webhook Retry Policy:**
- `sync-so-webhook` MUST mirror `poll-dialog-shots` retry logic. In multi-speaker scenes with `target_coords`, a terminal Sync.so failure must retry with `force_coords=true`, `deterministic_coords=true`, and `frame_number_override=round((start+end)/2*24)`. It must never downgrade that turn to `auto_detect`, because that can animate the wrong face and trigger the multi-speaker integrity guard.

Idempotency: dialog_shots state is single source of truth; `state.refunded` boolean prevents double-refund; `syncJobs.refunded` boolean in `audio_plan.twoshot` does the same for legacy path.

**June 2026 fix — 3-speaker pipeline regression:**
- `probeMp4Dims` (`_shared/twoshot-face-map.ts`) now does a 2-phase probe: head-range `bytes=0-786431` first, tail-range `bytes=-524288` as fallback for Hailuo/Replicate MP4s that place `moov` at the end. Logs `probe-result … phaseA=… phaseB=… dims=…`.
- `compose-dialog-segments` bounds-clamps speaker coords into the inner 90% of the probed plate (no-op when coords already inside frame → 1/2-speaker scenes unaffected).
- `sync-so-webhook` E.5 ladder gate switched from `isMultiSpeaker (>=2)` to `speakerCount >= 3`. 1- and 2-speaker scenes keep the full `coords-pro → auto-pro → auto-standard` ladder. 3+ speaker scenes still block `auto-*` by default but get a single "last-ditch-lite" `auto-pro` retry on pass 0 if every pass failed with `provider_unknown_error` / `face_not_found` — better one moving mouth than a fully-frozen scene.
- Cosmetic: `console.warn(…retries=${retryCount}…)` at the failure tail referenced an undefined variable; now `retries=${passRetryCount}/${aggregateRetryCount}`. Previously crashed the webhook response with `ReferenceError`, polluting Sync.so retry queue.
